---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
	title="prune skill"
	description="The prune skill finds CSS classes defined in a Tideway project but never used, so stylesheets don't accumulate dead rules."
	active="prune"
>
	<article class="doc">
		<p class="doc__eyebrow">Skill</p>
		<h1 class="doc__title">prune</h1>
		<p class="doc__lead">
			Finds CSS classes a project defines but no longer uses, so hand-written stylesheets don't
			accumulate dead rules. Strict BEM makes it reliable: every selector is a single flat class, so
			each rule maps to exactly one distinctive, searchable name.
		</p>

		<section class="doc__section">
			<h2 class="doc__section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="doc__list">
				<p class="doc__item">
					A bundled detector scans every <code class="doc__code">.css</code> file for defined classes,
					then searches the project's markup and scripts for each one.
				</p>
				<p class="doc__item">
					It reports two groups: <strong>Unused</strong> (no reference anywhere) and
					<strong>Possibly dynamic</strong> (see below).
				</p>
				<p class="doc__item">
					Findings are reported first; classes are removed only on your go-ahead, and it's safe to do
					under version control.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="doc__section">
			<h2 class="doc__section-title">The one caveat: dynamic class names</h2>
			<p class="doc__text">
				A class can be live without its full name ever appearing in the source — when markup builds it
				at runtime: <code class="doc__code">`card--$&#123;variant&#125;`</code>,
				<code class="doc__code">clsx("card", isOpen &amp;&amp; "card--open")</code>, or other string
				construction. Such a class looks unused to a text search.
			</p>
			<p class="doc__text">
				The detector flags these as <strong>Possibly dynamic</strong>: the exact name isn't found, but
				its prefix (<code class="doc__code">card--</code>) does appear. These are never removed on the
				report alone — the construction site is checked first to confirm the full name can't be
				produced there.
			</p>
		</section>
	</article>
</DocsLayout>
